_With a fancy new pipe stand to use, the drawer organizer I had sliced into a remote control tray was looking brutish …_

<img style="display:none;" src="https://Moondeer.micro.blog/uploads/2020/43898c0386.jpg" />
<p>
{{<glightbox src="https://Moondeer.micro.blog/uploads/2020/66ac456492.jpg" alt="Old Tray" gallery="remote-tray" >}}
</p>

_So I made a new one out of Wenge and Bloodwood_

<p>
{{<glightbox src="https://Moondeer.micro.blog/uploads/2020/c285d7f199.jpg" alt="Bare Remote Tray" gallery="remote-tray" >}}
{{<glightbox src="https://Moondeer.micro.blog/uploads/2020/43898c0386.jpg" alt="Loaded Remote Tray" gallery="remote-tray" >}}
</p>

_A look at my finest decorative knotting achievement, a collar I made for **Dugan**. The bulk of the collar is a double-edge plait. I invented knots to form each of the bear shapes. I then held my nose and stitched the bears to the braid._

<img style="display:none;" src="https://Moondeer.micro.blog/uploads/2020/8a98df00f4.jpg" />
<p>
{{<glightbox src="https://Moondeer.micro.blog/uploads/2020/8a98df00f4.jpg" alt="The back of the collar I made for Dugan" gallery="dugan-collar" >}}
	{{<glightbox src="https://Moondeer.micro.blog/uploads/2020/17c91f15dd.jpg" alt="The front of the collar I made for Dugan" gallery="dugan-collar" >}}
</p>

_The dancing bears I used as reference_

<p>
{{<glightbox src="https://Moondeer.micro.blog/uploads/2020/8e16fd1ffd.jpg" alt="The Grateful Dead dancing bears" gallery="dugan-collar" >}}
